The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 2 Reading players get death threats

Reading: Police are investigating death threats sent to the two Reading players involved in incidents that left Chelseas top two goalkeepers hospitalised with injuries. 

Ibrahima Sonko and Stephen Hunt have received a number of threatening letters at Readings training ground. 

We are going to kill you for what you did to our keepers, the a Reading newspaper quoted one of the letters as saying. 

The club is helping us with our inquiry and the matter is being investigated, Thames Valley Police said in a statement on Thursday. 

